commitResults.messageBody:
Storage was originally a wrapper around an ArrayList of tasks, which
is more accurately represented as TaskList.

FileHandler, responsible for saving/loading tasks, has been renamed
to Storage to better reflect its role.

commitResults.messageBody:
The code contains inconsistent indentation, improper naming
conventions, unused imports, and misformatted JavaDocs.

These issues reduce readability and make maintenance harder.

Fix indentation, enforce naming conventions,
remove unused imports, and correct JavaDocs.

This improves code consistency without changing functionality.

commitResults.messageTitle: refactor: improve Parser readability and consistency
commitResults.messageBody:
Parser currently has inline regex patterns and inconsistent method
access. This makes future modifications harder and reduces code
clarity.

Extract regex patterns into named constants (`DESC`, `FROM`,
`TO`, `BY`) and make helper methods consistently `private`.

This keeps the code cleaner and more maintainable without changing
behavior.

commitResults.messageTitle: feat: Add TaskType enum for better task handling
commitResults.messageBody:
Replaced string-based task types with TaskType enum to prevent typos
and ensure valid task types.

This makes the code clearer and easier to maintain.

commitResults.messageTitle: refactor: update AddTaskCommand to use TaskType and factory methods
commitResults.messageBody:
Replaced overloaded constructors with factory methods
(`createTodo()`, `createDeadline()`, `createEvent()`) for cleaner
task creation.

Updated AddTaskCommand to use TaskType enum instead of raw strings,
improving type safety and readability.

commitResults.messageTitle: refactor: update Parser to use AddTaskCommand factory methods
commitResults.messageBody:
Modified Parser to use `createTodo()`, `createDeadline()`, and
`createEvent()` instead of direct constructor calls.

This ensures consistent task creation and improves readability.
